power and gave rise to a pernicious form of armed neoliberalism. Their violent incursion into Barrancabermeja's civil society beginning in the 1980s decimated the city's social networks, destabilized life for its residents, and destroyed its working-class organizations. As a result, community leaders are now left clinging to the toothless discourse of human rights, which cannot effectively challenge the status quo. In this stark book, Gill captures the grim reality and precarious future of Barrancabermeja and other places ravaged by neoliberalism and violence.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aHuman rightszColombiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aLabor disputes - Colombia - Barrancabermeja - History - 20th century. 0aLabor disputeszColombiazBarrancabermejaxHistoryy20th century. 0aWorking classzColombiaxHistoryy20th century. 4aChoice Magazine Outstanding Academic Title. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070808040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822374701zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822374701423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822374701.jpg  a978-3-11-070808-0  DUK Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles